Betechified Frontend Development Project: Interactive Portfolio Website (HTML, CSS, JavaScript)

Project Overview
In this project, you will build a fully responsive and interactive personal portfolio website using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
 The portfolio should showcase User profile, skills, projects, and contact information with smooth transitions and basic interactivity (like form validation, dark mode toggle, or animations).

Learning Objectives
Structure and organize content using semantic HTML5.


Style and layout pages using modern CSS (Flexbox, Grid, transitions).


Implement interactivity using JavaScript (DOM manipulation, event handling).


Apply responsive design techniques for all screen sizes.


Use creativity and best practices in modern front-end development.



🪜 Step-by-Step Walkthrough
Step 1: Set Up Project Folder
 Create a folder named portfolio-project with:
index.html


style.css


script.js


images/ (for photos, icons, etc.)


Step 2: HTML Structure
 Include:
Navbar (Logo + Menu)


Hero Section (name, role, and call-to-action button)


About Section


Skills Section (can use icons or progress bars)


Projects Section (cards with hover effects)


Contact Section (form that validates input with JS)


Footer


Step 3: CSS Styling
 Use Flexbox/Grid for layout and responsive design.
 Add smooth hover transitions and animations.
Step 4: JavaScript Features
 Include at least 3 JS interactions, such as:
Dark/Light mode toggle


Responsive mobile menu


Form validation


Scroll reveal animation


Dynamic project filter/search


Step 5: Make It Responsive
 Ensure the site looks good on both desktop and mobile.

 Deliverables
index.html, style.css, and script.js files


Working hosted demo (e.g., via GitHub Pages or Netlify)


3–5 minutes walkthrough video


Presentation slides (Google Slides or PowerPoint)
A Flier containing the headshot of active members (you can design this using Canvas.



